## Key Insights

### Balance of Scalability & Reliability
Systems must carefully balance scaling capabilities with reliability measures. Implementing auto-scaling mechanisms while ensuring fault tolerance through circuit breakers is crucial.

### Performance vs Consistency Trade-offs
High-performance systems often require trade-offs between consistency and availability, following CAP theorem principles.

### Database Design Complexity
Effective database design requires careful consideration of normalization/denormalization strategies to optimize read/write performance.

